      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOND GIRL (3) finished fourth last start, beaten 16 metres at Kilmore over 1690m. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Won't find this any harder and she can play a major role in the outcome. BLISSFULL LILLY (1) settled handy but didn't finish off well enough when 11th in a 1720m race at Melton last start, beaten 40 metres. Kept up to the mark with a subsequent placing at the trials. Meets an easier field and is capable of taking this out if she can reproduce her win five starts back. DELTA STARZ (5) is worth another chance after a last-start ninth over 1680m at Terang a week ago. Can bounce back. FREAK OUT (4) is better than his last-start tenth over 1650m at Bendigo. Worth another chance.",
